-- World Bank Gives Mozambique $85 Million in Budget Support, O Pais Reports
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2010-12-21T04:46:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/world-bank-gives-mozambique-85-million-in-budget-support-o-pais-reports.html
The World Bank agreed to pay $85
million for Mozambique’s budget support for 2011, O Pais
reported, citing a statement from the bank.  The money will be used for the southern African country’s
second plan for poverty alleviation, the Maputo-based newspaper
said. The World Bank has been supporting Mozambique’s national
budget since 2004, according to the report.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
